properties.NAME: Palisaded hilltop enclosure, south-south-east of Dirt Low, Castleton
properties.SUMMARY: Eight-sided palisaded hilltop enclosure of either Iron Age or Romano-British date; now a scheduled monument.

properties.NAME: Smalldale Old Hall, Small Dale, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: House, now two houses, dating from 1670 with later 17th century addition and various later alterations.

properties.NAME: Long Rake Founder and Shack Pit, aka Batham Pot, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: High priority lead mining site with visible remains of shafts and hillocks.

properties.NAME: Lead Working (and Long Rake Mine), north of Potter Barn, Bradwell
properties.MONTYPE: LEAD MINE, LEAD WORKINGS, WASHING FLOOR
properties.SUMMARY: Lead mining site worked since 1670, including remains of washing floors and hillocks.

properties.NAME: Moorfurlong Lead Mine, north-east of Moorbrook View, Bradwell
properties.MONTYPE: LEAD MINE, SHAFT, WASHING FLOOR, BUDDLE
properties.SUMMARY: Important lead mine, where the primary archaeological interest is underground

properties.NAME: Enclosure, north of Hulmes Vale Farm, Tideswell
properties.SUMMARY: Circular enclosure of possibly later prehistoric date.

properties.NAME: Moss Rake / Royal Oak Mine, west of Wheston House, Tideswell and Peak Forest
properties.MONTYPE: LEAD WORKINGS, RAKE, HORSE ENGINE, DEWPOND
properties.SUMMARY: Large area of lead mining including various features such as a gin circle and a crushing wheel.

properties.NAME: Moss Rake / Royal Oak Mine, west of Wheston House, Tideswell and Peak Forest
properties.MONTYPE: LEAD WORKINGS, RAKE, HORSE ENGINE, DEWPOND
properties.SUMMARY: Large area of lead mining including various features such as a gin circle and a crushing wheel.

properties.NAME: Enclosure, south-east of Hulmes Vale Farm, Tideswell
properties.SUMMARY: Undated enclosure identified from an aerial photograph.  Precise location of earthwork is unknown.

properties.NAME: Pic Tor End Mine, east of Berrystall House, Hazlebadge
properties.SUMMARY: Lead mine worked from 1750 until 1809; surface remains destroyed in 1988-1989.

properties.NAME: Earl and Hill Rakes, Nall Hole Mine and Cow Hole, Tophole Road, Hazlebadge
properties.MONTYPE: LEAD MINE, RAKE, ENGINE HOUSE, COE?, FIELD BARN
properties.SUMMARY: Extensive lead rake worked in the 18th to 19th century.  Most of the rake has been reworked.

properties.NAME: Shuttle Rake, Tideswell, Bradwell and Hazlebadge
properties.MONTYPE: RAKE, SHAFT, SPOIL HEAP, CRUSHING CIRCLE
properties.SUMMARY: Post medieval lead mining rake; all of which now remains is hillocks and shafts.  The eastern side has been restored.

properties.NAME: Berrystall and Scrin Rakes, and Chance Mine, 730m south-west of Hartlemoor Farm, Hazlebadge and Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: Reworked area of lead rake with some remaining features including hillocks and shafts.

properties.NAME: Lime Kiln and Quarry, Bradwell Moor, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: Lime kiln and quarry, possibly late 19th to early 20th century in date.

properties.NAME: Lime Kiln and Quarry, Bradwell Moor, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: Lime kiln and quarry, possibly late 19th to early 20th century in date.

properties.NAME: Lime Kiln and Quarry, Bradwell Moor, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: Lime kiln and quarry, possibly late 19th to early 20th century in date.

properties.NAME: Lime Kiln and Quarry, Bradwell Moor, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: Lime kiln and quarry, possibly late 19th to early 20th century in date.

properties.NAME: Enclosures (?site of), south-west of Hope Cement Works, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: Post medieval circular and irregular enclosures, destroyed c.1962.  Precise location of enclosures is unknown.

properties.NAME: Hope Cement Works, Hope
properties.MONTYPE: LIMESTONE QUARRY, SHALE WORKING SITE, CEMENT WORKS
properties.SUMMARY: Cement works built in 1929 and expanded in 1948, 1961 and 1969.

properties.NAME: Hazard Mine, Castleton
properties.MONTYPE: WINDING CIRCLE, LEAD MINE, MINE SHAFT
properties.SUMMARY: Partially removed post medieval mine. Remaining features include a gin circle, an engine shaft and part of a belland yard.

properties.NAME: Dirtlow Rake, south of Castleton
properties.MONTYPE: CRUSHING CIRCLE, LEAD MINE, COE, HORSE WHIM, RAKE, MINE SHAFT
properties.SUMMARY: Largely reworked  lead rake which retains an intact area with shafts, a coe, a crushing circle and a gin circle.  Documented as active in 1538.

properties.NAME: Penny mine engine shaft and Wham Rake, north of Ox Low barrow, Castleton
properties.SUMMARY: Preserved remains of shafts and hillocks and ruined belland yards along a lead rake.

properties.NAME: Ox Low Oval Barrow, north of Clear-the-Way Mine, Peak Forest
properties.MONTYPE: CONTRACTED INHUMATION, CIST, LONG BARROW?, OVAL BARROW?
properties.SUMMARY: Neolithic oval barrow excavated pre 1877; evidence of re-use in the Bronze Age.  Now a scheduled monument.

properties.NAME: Lime Kiln and Quarry, south of Clement Lane, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: Late 18th or early 19th century lime kiln and quarry; disused by 1880.

properties.NAME: New Venture Mine, Bradwell Moor, Bradwell
properties.MONTYPE: MINE SHAFT, DRESSING FLOOR, LEAD MINE
properties.SUMMARY: Post medieval lead mine with remaining features such as shafts, opencuts and a dressing floor.

properties.NAME: Lime kiln and quarries, east of Clear-the-way Mine, Castleton
properties.SUMMARY: Circular post medieval pudding-pie limekiln, disused by 1880.

properties.NAME: ?Cropmark features, Dirtlow Rake, Castleton
properties.SUMMARY: A possible enclosure and other cropmarks were identified from an aerial photograph; re-interpreted as probably natural.

properties.NAME: Hollandtwine Mine (site of), Dirtlow Rake, Castleton
properties.MONTYPE: COE, WINDING CIRCLE, MINE SHAFT, CRUSHING CIRCLE, DRAINAGE LEVEL, LEAD MINE
properties.SUMMARY: Approximate site of a post medieval lead mine complex destroyed by recent reworking.

properties.NAME: Lime kiln (disused) and associated quarry pits, Dirtlow Rake, Castleton
properties.SUMMARY: The remains of a disused lime kiln and several associated quarry pits were recorded during survey in 1992.  The lime kiln was already out of use by c. 1880.

properties.NAME: ?Romano-British settlement, Dirtlow Rake, Castleton
properties.SUMMARY: Low stony banks, enclosures and lynchets; probably a settlement site of either 1st/2nd millennium BC date or Romano-British

properties.NAME: New Venture West End Mine, Siggate, Bradwell Moor
properties.SUMMARY: Good example of a small-sized lead vein. A High Priority Lead Site.

properties.NAME: Smalldale Mines, Cresswellpart Lane, Smalldale, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: Three isolated hillocks of a Lead Mine. A High Priority Lead Mining Site.

properties.NAME: Moss Rake - Southfield Mines, Outlands Road, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: Site of an Old Lead Mine. A High Priority Lead Mining Site.

properties.NAME: Lambpart Vein, Batham Gate, Little Hucklow
properties.SUMMARY: Hillocks and a part-filled shaft within and adjacent to a belland yard.

properties.NAME: Lambpart Mines, Lambpart Lane, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: Hillocks and shafts of a former lead mine, with a possible ruined coe.

properties.NAME: Pin Dale lead side veins, c.200m south-west of Pindale Farm, Castleton
properties.MONTYPE: LEAD WORKINGS, RAKE, MINE SHAFT, DRESSING FLOOR
properties.SUMMARY: Area of post-medieval opencut mining comprised of side veins and open shafts; now a scheduled monument.

properties.NAME: Hartledale Mine, Clement Lane, Bradwell
properties.MONTYPE: WINDING CIRCLE, MINE SHAFT, CRUSHING CIRCLE
properties.SUMMARY: Walled gin circle with adjacent shaft.  A crushing wheel has recently been placed next to the gin circle.

properties.NAME: Bird Lead Mine, Siggate, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: An oval engine shaft of a former lead mine.

properties.NAME: Oxlow Rake, Castleton and Peak Forest
properties.MONTYPE: LEAD MINE, WALL, COE, MINE, ORE STORE, WATER CHANNEL, BUDDLE, DAM, WASHING FLOOR, CRUSHING FLOOR, WINDING CIRCLE
properties.SUMMARY: Extensive area of post-medieval lead workings and rakes comprised of shafts, open workings and hillocks.  The workings were active from at least 1605 until c.1900.

properties.NAME: Raddle Pits, 700m north-west of Berrystall Lodge, Bradwell
properties.SUMMARY: Post medieval lead mine with a preserved underground spiral staircase.

properties.NAME: Eldon Vein and Portaway Mine, Peak Forest
properties.MONTYPE: BELLAND YARD WALL, LEAD MINE, DAM
properties.SUMMARY: Partially walled belland yard and dam for a large pond within an area of high priority lead mining.

properties.NAME: Cop Rake Lead Mine, Bradwell
properties.MONTYPE: LEAD MINE, FLUORSPAR MINE, MINE SHAFT, DRESSING FLOOR, HORSE ENGINE
properties.SUMMARY: Post medieval lead mining complex recorded as a high priority site and scheduled.  Documentary evidence indicates it was worked as early as 13th century.
